quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  4,105,"We have sent down the Book to you [O Prophet] in truth, so that you may judge between people, in accordance with what Allah has taught you. So do not be an advocate for the deceitful"
  4,106,"And seek forgiveness of Allah, for Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  4,107,"Do not argue on behalf of those who betray themselves, for Allah does not like the treacherous and sinful"
  4,108,"They seek to hide from people but they do not seek to hide from Allah, although He is with them when they devise plans to say things that are displeasing to Him. Indeed, Allah encompasses all what they do"
  4,109,"Here you are, you are those who argue on their behalf in the life of this world, but who will argue on their behalf before Allah on the Day of Resurrection, or who will be their defender"
  4,110,"Whoever commits evil or wrongs himself, then seeks Allah’s forgiveness will find Allah All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  4,111,"And whoever commits a sin, he only commits it against himself. And Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  4,112,"But whoever commits an offense or a sin, then blames it on an innocent person, will surely bear the guilt of slander and flagrant sin"